	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hey once again, I've tried to program Donald in Maui Mallard (NTSC hack) on a 27C322 EPROM but the ROM is 3MB, so I did the famous SNES trick- 3MB of data + last 1/3 of data = 4MB of data to fill the whole memory. So after I soldered the IC into my PCB, it doesn't work unfortunately.... There must be some rom-related issue because I verified the chip 2 times and even by comparing it using Total Commander and everything was programmed 100% correct, so what should I do in this case?? And to be more clear- of course I connected A19 &amp; A20 to cartridge connector so there's no problem in that. Please for any replies and advices. Big thanks in advance!!

		

